# Python Style And Architecture

- Use Python 3.11+ features when practical.
- Add type hints on public APIs and keep interfaces explicit.
- Keep modules small and focused; apply single-responsibility design.
- Enforce formatting and linting with Ruff (`format` and `check`).
- Prefer readable code over clever one-liners.
- Add concise docstrings for public classes and functions.
